==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subtend
<hw>Sub*tend"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Subtended</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Subtending</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>subtendere</ets>;
<ets>sub</ets> under + <ets>tendere</ets> to stretch, extend. See
<er>Tend</er>.]</ety> <def>To extend under, or be opposed to; <as>as,
the line of a triangle which <ex>subtends</ex> the right angle; the
chord <ex>subtends</ex> an arc</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subtense</ent>⟦br⟧
